The paper deals with the problem of sparse signal and image recovery from compressed measurements, which is a common problem in several areas of computer science such as information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), signal processing (cs.SP), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The proposed algorithm is based on a nonconvex regularization technique, which is a popular research topic in these sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SP, and cs.NA, in that order.
